cds_process_report.Rd

Extract data from a CDS PDF report.

Usage

cds_process_report(school, file, ocr = FALSE)

Arguments

school

Name of the school, to be checked for in the document.

file

Path to the PDF report.

ocr

Logical; if TRUE, will use Optical Character Recognition to extract text from the file.

Value

A list containing the locations of items identified in the report and the values extracted from the report.

Examples

file <- "../../reports/text/Yale University/cds2008_2009_1.txt"
if (file.exists(file)) {
  values <- cds_process_report("Yale University", file)
  values[1:10]
}
